04/01/2010
TEHRAN, Iran -- Security forces have arrested ten Turkish citizens on charges of fuel smuggling, the Anadolu news agency reported on Sunday (January 3rd). 
The group entered neighbouring Iran on December 31st through the Esendere border checkpoint, in the city of Yuksekova. 
Iranian authorities have since seized their passports. 
Hakkari Governor Muammer Turker says efforts are under way to get the ten released. 
(Xinhua, Anadolu news agency - 03/01/10)
